<br>
I think Verant was right in giving pet hold to us at 59.  Why?  Let me explain.  There are so many pet owners out there that just have no clue how to control their pets.  We all know it, we have all seen it.<br>
<br>
In my opinion, /pet hold is just another tool to make a pet owner's life easier.  BUT, while it makes pet owners' jobs easier, it also opens the door for more incompetent pet owners.<br>
<br>
For example...a mage (or any other pet owner) parks pet in a spot using /pet hold, sits down to med, does /pet attack after assisting on Main Assist, mob dies, pet goes back to it's spot.  If adds come along and start beating on the pet, chanter can mez them and pet owner never has to worry about clearing the pet's hate list, or backing the pet off so the pet doesn't attack them back.  If an added mob casts an aoe that hits the owner while he's medding, and chanter goes to mez that mob, pet owner doesn't have to worry about pulling pet off the mob.  <br>
<br>
Now sure, this IS easier, and I am definitely looking forward to the day when I can use this command.  In my opinion though, IF this command was given to pet owners at a much earlier level, either pre 50 or even pre 55, pet owners would NOT learn how to back off their pets in high level groups and raids, like I mentioned above.  Pet owners would NOT learn the skills and techniques of proper pet control and working with enchanters and the like, pet owners would become overly dependent on this skill and get &quot;lazy&quot; and we would just have an overall higher level of incompetent pet owners all around.<br>
<br>
So, I salute Verant for giving mages this skill at 59.  Because by the time you're 59, you've made a reputation for yourself as a pet owner, you've learned the skills of proper pet control, and whether or not you have this skill, you CAN control your pet in any given situation.<br>
<br>
