<br>
While I agree with you that it would seem that melee classes are not as thrilling as Casters, they kind of go hand in hand. A caster cannot survive long enough without a melee in front taking the abuse. Mages... are kind of odd that way in that we come preequipped with a built in tank. We have variety, we have damage potential in either melee or magic. We can now heal, we can now summon armor, and weapons, and all the other things we've always wanted to. We not only have mana regeneration, but POSITIVE FLOW on the transvergence rod. Even with all of this, there are aspects that have been around that have really irked people in general.<br>
<br>
Kunark came around, and Verant didn't listen, or Verant was blind, or their CEO had a bad day, or something. Melee classes got looked at and upgraded heavily, and Casters got.. nothing. Magicians themselves got 4 'play' spells out of.. how many? Like 16? Something like that. Several spells are useless (Read: 52 and 58 Fire pets). Some spells they didn't think through properly (Phantom Armor and it's 4 gem reagent cost), and some they made impossible to get (Burnout 4, Water pets, Muzzle). They added some nice things like the Post-50 Focus items, except.. noone seeks them, and they're extremely hard to get. Some, like the Staff of Air, use the same Crown from the Plane of Air that the Epics use. <br>
<br>
When they brought the epics out, we mages got an extremely powerfull boost. Our epic is with us, ALWAYS. Now, I don't mind a difficult or hard quest for this, but when my fellow players rip off a cloak off a rare random spawn (Quillmane) or one component drops off a mob that exists only.. once a month, and the staff is rare on him still (Innoruk, Earth staff), it's like.. why bother? We see Rogues having to get 4 robes, fight 1 fight, and viola, Epic! We see our epic, and maybe.. 5 people on our server have it. That sucks. It took me until level 53 to even SEE a magician with an epic. It bodes not well for the class when all these cool toys come out, and we're basically teased with them, because of the obscene difficulty in getting the pieces. No other class has to put up with so much crap for their Epic as Magicians do, and that's a huge gap between our epic and the next.<br>
<br>
Now, most of us Magicians have been understanding, and tried to point out places where the class was being handled badly. We as a comunity (or individuals) have pointed out the pet pathing issue. This I wager has been around for a LONG time. While we as mages are capable of dealing damage without our pets, it is sort of like asking a warrior to give up their uber weapon and wield a rusty sword. As a class, we are not doing our jobs of dealing damage (which is part of what we do) without our pets. We have commented, and they tell us they'll look at it. We've reminded, and they take a look at it. We ask what's being done, and they say 'Hey, here you go, a 'Summon Companion' spell!'. We go Great! and as the only pet class with this spell, we feel prim and proper once again. This doesn't fix the problem, but at least we can now work around it and still have our pets, sometimes. Once Verant discovers how great a job we've managed with this one spell, they go &quot;Here, all pet classes shall now recieve this spell.&quot; We look on aghast. <br>
<br>
The part that gets me about this Summon Companion spell is that there are many cases where it is utterly and totally useless. Pathing bugs exist in droves around the world. Sit down in a corner, stand up, and your pet that you had pacing nearby runs off. Just Standing up, not even moving. And by the time you realize that he's gone, and click on the Summon Companion spell gem, it's too late. He's in combat, and you're now dead. Summon Companion is also useless in areas where you're stopped and fighting a camp. How usefull is that spell when you send your pet to attack, and he goes 15 blocks around to the right to get 1 block to the left? Oops, he's got aggro for 15 other things, *wham* dead once again. Nothing you did wrong, asside from not memorize the invisible paths earlier.<br>
<br>
So we come to Velious. Velious is nice, it's good, it has some usefull things to it.. DoT's.. never used a DoT in my career til Velious, and it's not all that usefull, having only 2 DoT's. We get some DD's, we get 3 play spells once again. Monster Summoning. Now, while I do get a kick out of being in lower level zones and having a griffon pet or sand giant walking around, it's pretty much useless overall. You can't predict your pet's type (not even influence it with your focus items), and their level bracket is only usefull right about the time you get the spell. Yay :P Now, a new problem we face.. creatures are highly magic resistant. We got some of that in Kunark with the Reavers, but they seem to be isolated. Velious the problem was widespread. Oh well, at least we have our pets? Well, only in certain situations. Oh well <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Now, they did revisit this and add features that made it easier for them to selectively make mobs harder to cast on, and brought down the overall level of the resistances, but only on major creatures, as I gather. Not only that, but we seemed to miss out on some spells like Improved INvisibility, so that they could give us some more play spells like the Monster line. Me, while I enjoy the Monster line, would rather have had Improved Invisibility.<br>
<br>
With Luclin, we FINALLY started getting the spells we've been asking for. Armor spells for the pets, pet heals (which to me, we got the best deal on as it uses our mantra of Conjuration). We got usefull summons like the Elemental Blanket (+15 MR. Pet can wear two. That plus the Dagger of Symbols.. who's going to turn down +45 magic resistance for their pets?). We can summon a Shield! Finally, we can do all sorts of things that we've always wanted to do.... except that pathing STILL sucks, they didn't learn thing one of what they should've done from their previous times. Not only that, one thing that seriously crimps our style, lack of pet when zoning/camping in/etc, the new class Beastlords can do. And, to slap it in our face almost, WIZARDS, of all people, get this fancy little visual buff that won't aggro, won't be killed except by AoE, or in direct combat in PvP. It has a massive drawback if it does die, but normally, a Mob will not kill this thing.<br>
<br>
I personally got a nice good taste of the failing of Mages to have that skill when I was hunting Owlbears in Hollowshade Moor. All the way deep in their cavern, I (and the zone) get punted. Pet goes poof, and I'm sitting there going 'great'. Log back in, and of course due to the long loading times and such, once I log in and actually get a screen to look at the world, I have Aggro. My pet can deal with these things in 30 seconds, but me, naw.. these things summon, they hit in the high 80's, and are only level 25-30. Here I am, going to be beatdown, because Verant's zone crashed, and I went Linkdead. Fortunately, Jboots carry me faster than Owlbears travel, so I live, but I'm sure we can all agree that every once in a while, after trying and trying for a 'max level pet' and getting it, the instant we go Linkdead, weh've just murdered ourselves, and our chances for getting back in the game alive. I wonder if this is to be our weakness, a routine beatdown, for having the best pet in the game. Either way, no matter what they say, a Magician is not godlike in their ability. They can do many things, but what we can't do hurts us badly.<br>
<br>
Astro has it down pretty well. I don't think any of us is asking for Verant to make us some uber-god class. Knowing now that these things Can be done, it would be nice for them to revisit them instead of press headlong into the next wave while ignoring the core of what their business is made up of (ie: those original classes). You know, I don't even think that the added penalties to Call of the Hero would be so bad IF it were balanced across the board. We simply want someone over at Verant to wake up, go 'wait', and rethink some of the old things that have been problematic, and bring them up with the rest. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uvalandel.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Valandel</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#333333>(12/10/01 5:51:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=53.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.theotaku.com/dragonball/animated/vegeta5.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_smile.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: the most signifcant message</span><hr size=1> Fact or Fiction?<br>
